description:
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to part of a dynamic and evolving Health Visiting team within the 0-19 Service in Wolverhampton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If yes; The Royal Wolverhampton NHS Trust is pleased to offer an opportunity for motivated Health Visitors to join our well-established service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have a recognised Health Visitor Qualification, V100/V300 Nurse Prescribing, up to date knowledge of the current national recommendations and public health agenda including the Healthy Child Programme, along with sound knowledge and experience of safeguarding children then this post could be for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Wolverhampton NHS trust is currently re-shaping the way Health Visitors work, looking at new and innovative practices to improve Child Health in Wolverhampton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a range of Band 6 Health Visiting posts across the city, offering good professional development opportunities, working with diverse populations. We are developing innovative models of working with our families and partner agencies to offer high quality care to achieve positive outcomes for families in Wolverhampton. As part of the new 0-19 Service Model we are developing a Single Point of Access for clients. The health visiting service will be supporting this process offering fantastic opportunities for flexible working on a rotational basis to provide 8-8 cover.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are ambitious and a forward thinking employer and this is a great opportunity for the right individuals to join us in our success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates will receive opportunities to develop clinical, management, leadership and partnership working skills. We have a robust preceptorship programme and offer restorative supervision alongside safeguarding supervision to provide enhanced support for working with complex families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Car owner/driver essential and you must be able to meet the travel requirements of the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Victoria Marriott Health Visitor Team Leader on 01902 444429/07768535847 victoria.marriott@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
